
[1]adrogation

   ADROGA'TION, n. [L. ad and rogo, to ask. See Interrogate and Rogation.]

   A species of adoption in ancient Rome, by which a person, capable of
   choosing for himself, was admitted into the relation of a son. So
   called from the questions put to the parties.
